        <headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued July 7 at 4:08AM EDT until July 7 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Dangerous swimming conditions expected. Waves of 3 to 5
feet will subside to 2 to 3 feet by Monday afternoon. A strong
southward flowing longshore current is expected, in addition to
life-threatening rip currents withing the sandbars and structural
currents near piers or breakwalls (particularly the north side).

* WHERE...Northern Berrien county.

* WHEN...Through this evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong currents can pull swimmers into deeper water
and high waves can sweep people off piers.
</description>
        <instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions.
Do not venture out on piers.</instruction>
